message.content: One of the most significant events that happened in Albania in the past 20 years is the accession of the country to the North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO). In 2009, Albania became a full member of NATO, marking a significant milestone in the country's development and integration into the Euro-Atlantic community. This event solidified Albania's ties with Western European countries and demonstrated its commitment to Euro-Atlantic values, stability, and security. The NATO membership has had a positive impact on Albania's political, economic, and security spheres, while also enhancing its international standing.
